---
notes: To make it easier, the Earl Grey-infused gin can be made in a large quantity ahead of time. Pour 1 liter gin over 1/4 cup Earl Grey tea leaves in a glass or metal bowl, and allow to steep for 2 hours. Afterward, strain gin back into its bottle. Do not press tea leaves to extract excess gin, as this can make the infusion bitter.
---

Sprinkle the @earl grey tea leaves{1%teaspoon} over the @gin{3%oz} in a #small glass{}, and set aside to steep for ~{2%hours}.

Pour 1/4 to 1/2 inch of @white sugar{1/4%inch} onto a #small shallow plate{}. Moisten the rims of #martini glasses{2} with a @lemon{1%wedge}, dip the moistened glasses into the sugar; set aside.

Strain the infused @gin, @lemon juice{1.5%oz}, and @simple syrup{2%oz} into a #cocktail shaker{} over @ice{}. Cover, and shake until the outside of the shaker has frosted. Strain into the rimmed glasses to serve.
